&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At GT’s Living Foods, our Fill/Pack Mixers (I) ensure that every batch of Kombucha is handcrafted with the highest quality ingredients to make the product our consumers know and love. In addition to occasionally performing the responsibilities of a Fill/Pack Mixing Assistant in alignment with business needs, Fill/Pack Mixers (I) are responsible for understanding the formulaic composition of our products and incorporating all ingredients accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Release and initiate production order, including keg materials, physically and systematically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize electrical panel to perform mixing of necessary ingredients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble and inspect components of mixing equipment to ensure equipment is ready for use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with other internal departments to confirm and communicate the production schedule to Fill/Pack Mixing Assistants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reference production schedule to create a list of necessary ingredients, and validate picking list prior to providing to Fill/Pack Mixing Assistants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manually and systematically verify that the ingredients and labels collected and consumed correspond with the production schedule, including variances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation of pH, Brix, color and taste of each batch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine cleanings of mixing equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any issues regarding equipment malfunction, system errors, and downtime to management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure cleanliness of work area to maintain a safe work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
